  and toggles `.dark` class based on `theme.isDark`; uses the existing `"no-transitions"` trick.
- Module-level call `applyCustomTheme(getStoredThemeId())` — runs at import time to prevent FOUC.
- `subscribe(listener)` — registers listener + cross-tab `storage` event handler.
- `useCustomTheme()` — `useSyncExternalStore(subscribe, getSnapshot)`, returns
  `{ themeId, setThemeId, theme, themes }`.

```ts
export function useCustomTheme() {
  const snapshot = useSyncExternalStore(subscribe, getSnapshot);
  const setThemeId = useCallback((id: ThemeId) => {
    localStorage.setItem(STORAGE_KEY, id);
    applyCustomTheme(id, true);
    emitChange();
  }, []);
  return { themeId: snapshot.themeId, setThemeId, theme: getBuiltInTheme(snapshot.themeId), themes: BUILT_IN_THEMES } as const;
}
```

