# Custom Theme System — Implementation Plan

## Context

T3 Code currently has a minimal light/dark/system toggle (`hooks/useTheme.ts`) that simply
applies a `.dark` class to `<html>`. The task is to add a full named-theme system with three
built-in palettes ("t3-dark", "t3-light", "t3-midnight"), persistent selection, CSS custom
property application, and a settings-page theme selector with colour swatches.

The new system must:
- Keep the existing `.dark`-class mechanism working (Tailwind `dark:` utilities depend on it).
- Not touch build config or add new dependencies.
- Pass `bun lint` and `bun typecheck`.

---

## Architecture Decision

| Concern | Decision |
|---|---|
| Theme type definition | `packages/shared/src/theme.ts` (new subpath export, plain TS — no Effect Schema needed) |
| Dark-mode class | Managed inside `useCustomTheme` alongside `data-theme` attribute |
| React wiring | Thin `ThemeProvider` (React Context) placed in `routes/__root.tsx` |
| Existing `useTheme.ts` | Left unchanged; its import in `_chat.settings.tsx` is removed and replaced |
| CSS specificity | `[data-theme]` rules use `:root[data-theme="…"]` selector (specificity 0,2,0) so they beat the `@variant dark` block inside `:root` (also 0,2,0) via cascade order |
| localStorage key | `"t3code:custom-theme"` (follows existing `"t3code:…"` prefix convention) |

